<br>
<br>
Absolutely.  Newbie spamming of a few styles will not work at all with this class (unless you don't mind being performing sub-par).  But with selective use the the buffs and use of position and reactionary styles, the Savage can be very very effective. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#000000>- </font><a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc>Light Tanks of DAoC</a><font color=#000000> - </font><a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20>Savage General Discussion</a> <font color=#000000> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.3u<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

